oking girl</span><hr size=1> To begin with,I am not a man. As stupid as that sounds last time I checked I wasn't one.<br>
<br>
Next, I don't care how pointy some peoples's chins are because unless they are horriblely deformed, they are going to have jawbones, which will level out their chin.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, I never said the clothes lacked detail, I said they looked flat. Don't put words in my mouth. Unless her clothes are coated in some sort of waxey or plasticy substance I doubt if the ends of her shirt are going to curve up to little points.<br>
<br>
Next, a pant leg won't naturally bend like that unless there is something to bend over, and as far as I can see you make no direct indication on her left foot that the foot isn't following the curve in the pants.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I never said there was 'too much' of anything. I was very blunt, and even warned you I would be. If you were looking for sugar-coated comments, well, then your out of luck. You may have been saved from sharp remarks, but in the real world, true art critics aren't going to be nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mastatsan>Mastatsan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/19/02 4:46:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6932.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.host69.com/user/mastatsan/images/2nd_Armor_-_G-Crush.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Friendly looking girl</span><hr size=1> How the heck am I supposed to know you're not a man? o.O I see you... I see you all, in fact... that's how I know... yes... yes...<br>
<br>
Put on a pair of denim (or other rigid matieral) pants and look, the material won't fall over every cuve perfectly (like t-shirt type matierial would), it bends a little more than if it were just hanging over something... it's called a shoe.<br>
<br>
Looking flat is part of detail and shade in my dictionary, so you need to chill out and stop acting like I'm trying to be a jerk to you and &quot;put words in your mouth&quot; (might also help if you clarified what you meant by flat BEFORE I argued your opinion).  The clothes pointing like that is style, I got sick of drawing well-formed clothing, so now I deform it a little...<br>
<br>
and what I meant about the &quot;too much&quot; comment is when you were saying &quot;clothing is TOO flat&quot;... I can make my clothing as flat as I want it to be... you could say something more like &quot;the clothing looks flat&quot;... Still blunt, but it's a little... better sounding....<br>
<br>
